        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Storage that earns its footprint</h3><p>Corner solutions, pantry planning, utility cabinets, cutlery zones, appliance pockets, and tall units should support daily use, not just make the elevation look complete.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Better alignment with the rest of the home</h3><p>A kitchen sits inside a larger interiors story. Finish direction, openness, and visual weight should feel intentional when seen from dining, utility, or living spaces.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>Estimate-ready decision making</h3><p>The more clearly the customer defines layout, material direction, and storage intensity, the more useful the consultation and estimate become.</p></article>
