        <h2 class="bw-modular__title" style="font-size:clamp(24px, 3vw, 34px);">The strongest modular-kitchen projects follow a clear sequence</h2>
        <p class="bw-modular__copy">A kitchen becomes easier to design and easier to estimate when the brief develops in the right order. Layout leads, materials follow, and storage plus appliance planning complete the picture.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bw-modular__cards">
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>01. Read the room correctly</h3><p>Begin with wall lengths, service points, doors, windows, movement paths, and how many people typically use the kitchen at the same time.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>02. Choose the right layout family</h3><p>The correct layout should create the right mix of circulation, counter continuity, and storage volume before any styling discussion begins.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>03. Finalize carcass, shutters, and countertop</h3><p>Once the layout is fixed, the project can move into material choices that shape durability, maintenance, and budget direction.</p></article>
        <article class="bw-modular__card"><h3>04. Detail storage and appliances</h3><p>Tall units, pantry needs, corner accessories, built-in appliances, utility zones, and drawer types all change how complete the kitchen feels in daily use.</p></article>
